  "response": "Adding raw egg to milk is not generally recommended due to several health risks and considerations:\n\n1. Salmonella risk: Raw eggs can contain harmful bacteria like Salmonella, which can cause food poisoning.\n\n2. Food safety: Consuming raw eggs increases the chance of bacterial infection.\n\n3. Protein absorption: Cooked eggs are actually more easily digested and have better protein bioavailability.\n\n4. Potential alternatives: If you want to increase protein intake, consider:\n- Protein powders\n- Cooked eggs\n- Commercially prepared protein shakes\n- Greek yogurt\n\nIf you're interested in a protein-rich drink, it's safer to use pasteurized eggs or cook the eggs before adding them to milk.",
